SALESFORCE RELEASE NOTES
Show Search Results in an Interactive Map

Help users find the most suitable resource based on location by showing a map alongside search results. Map markers show essential details about the people, places, or things in the search results.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience editions where Criteria-Based Search and Filter is enabled.

Who: Users with the Criteria-Based Search and Filter system permission can configure and use criteria-based search and filter capabilities.

How: Add a search configuration with distance criteria. From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Criteria, and then select Criteria-Based Search and Filter. On the Search Configuration tab, click New. When you configure the distance criteria, turn on Show Map. Then select the field values for the map marker titles and descriptions.
